 At the top of the window, there is a menu bar with the following items:

- Standard Settings
- Advanced Settings
- Help

In the main area of the window, there are two sections:

- The left section contains a tree view of the different settings categories.
- The right section contains the controls for the selected setting.

The following is a list of the items in the tree view:

- User Interface
- Touch Bar
- Trackpad
- Notch / Action
- Menu Bar
- Window Snapping & Moving
- BTT Remote
- General
- Magic Mouse
- Keyboard
- Drawings / Gestures
- MIDI Settings
- Scripting BTT
- Web Server
- Normal Mouse

The following is a list of the controls in the right section:

- Show Menu Bar Icon (if you hide the icon you can access the preferences by starting BTT again)
- Show Dock Icon while running (may require restart)
- Font Sizes in the Main User Interface:
    - Increase / Decrease Base Font Size by:
    - pt
    - Reset BTT to Apply Changes
- App Side-Bar:
    - Use Default Dark Translucent Side-Bar
    - Restart BTT to Apply Changes
- Language & Region:
    - Language:
        - System Language (if available)
    - Region Settings
    - Restart BTT to Apply Changes
- Various things:
    - Only show recently used colors in side-bar color picker dropdown

At the bottom of the window, there is a button that says "Restore Defaults".